Defendant Zachery Thomas Slaten in court with attorney Valeria Lenise Taylor.  Defendant Zachery Thomas Slaten in custody.  Deann L Heard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Letter on behalf of defendant received and filed. PSI reviewed by parties. State placed negotiations on the record. Court finds the state has complied with the victim rights legislation. Statements made as to sentencing.  Additional statements by: Zachery Slaten.

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 6 YEARS, with credit for 91 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 3 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 3 YEARS.  

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 3 YEARS with the following conditions:

1) Court set restitution at zero;
2) Maintain employment of 20 hours per week. If not employed at least 20 hours per week be enrolled fulltime in school.
3) No driving without a valid license; 
4)  No contact with the victim. No contact with the following co-actors: Tameca Bryant, T.H. dob 9/14/97, Q.G. dob 7/14/00, M.L. dob 8/30/99, with the exception of T.Q. dob 11/04/98; 
5) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
6) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharges;
7) AODA Assessments and comply with recommended treatment or counseling;
8) Cognitive Thinking Programming;
9) Court ordered 90 days of condition time be imposed but STAYED to be used at the discretion of the agent.

If revoked, court costs, fees and surcharges be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds/ earnings.

If revoked, Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. The defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.

*Bail on deposit to be applied towards costs, fees and surcharges.
